(176639, 'EF9CFCCD-8A96-46B3-9E6A-1F3599587BE0', 'Well. That''s about right. Have a mini meal at 10:30...especially after one of your morning workout days. Handful of almonds and fruit and/or a protein shake. Peanut or almond butter. Just no refined sugars or flour. Also, you might get less hungry if you find a cereal with more real grains (granola that isn''t too sweet with lots o seeds or musli and add some berries to your yogurt). And no crappy sugary yogurt. Get the real stuff.  I can go on....trick is real food. Your trainer should have some good tips. ', 'David', 'Nitzan', '2015-07-27T08:25:05'),
